H0.text: The Hapsburg dynasty originated in which country. Austria

H1.text: The Hapsburg dynasty originated in which country. Germany

H2.text: The Hapsburg dynasty originated in which country. Hungary

H3.text: The Hapsburg dynasty originated in which country. Suiza

A4.text: Habsburg Castle, a fortress built in the 1020s in present-day Switzerland by Radbot of Klettgau, who named his fortress Habsburg.

A5.text: Before Rudolph rose to German king, the Habsburgs were Counts of Baden in what is today southwestern Germany and Switzerland.

A6.text: The progenitor of the House of Habsburg may have been Guntram the Rich, a count in the Breisgau who lived in the 10th century.
